wiki.content: The fourth song on Drake’s More Life playlist, “Jorja Interlude”, was first premiered on OVO Sound Radio’s “Episode 39” on March 18, 2017. The track features Jorja Smith, an up-and-coming singer-songwriter from the United Kingdom. “Get It Together,” which also features Smith, follows directly after this interlude. Towards the end the track features a sample from Drake’s 2011 soulful “Doing It Wrong,” specifically Stevie Wonder’s harmonica solo. According to Songfacts, artist Jorja Smith said to The London Sunday Times: "He sent me the song, but because I write my own stuff, it was, like, ‘This is really cool, but it’s not anything to do with me at the moment.’ And then, after about a year, I split up with my boyfriend, and I listened to the song again, and it was, like, ‘Aah, this is what he’s talking about – I get it’." Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
